{
  "doc_id": "53177",
  "text": "Recently, the worldwide live birth rate of 30% was recorded after transplantation for cryo-preserved ovarian tissue [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Women with cancers and endometriosis are at risk of POI and their conditions necessitate fertility cryopreservation options [CITATION_3] . The most common benefit of ovarian transplantation is the preservation of fertility and future endocrine function in young women undergoing cancer treatment [CITATION_4] . However, elective fertility cryopreservation for non-medical (social) reasons can be accepted as an option to postpone motherhood [CITATION_5] .",
